---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Recessed Lighting Calculator for Kitchen — How Many Lights? | CalcForDIY"
  description="Calculate how many recessed lights you need for a kitchen. Includes general ambient lighting plus task lighting over counters and island. Free, no signup."
>

  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebApplication",
    "name": "Recessed Lighting Calculator for Kitchen",
    "description": "Free kitchen lighting calculator that estimates fixture count for both general ambient lighting and task lighting over countertops and kitchen island.",
    "applicationCategory": "CalculatorApplication",
    "operatingSystem": "Web Browser",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD" }
  }
  </script>

  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How many recessed lights do I need for a 12x14 kitchen?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "For a standard 12x14 kitchen (168 square feet), targeting 50 foot-candles with standard 750-lumen fixtures requires roughly 15 ambient fixtures. If you add counter and island task lighting on top of that, your total fixture count will increase depending on your specific layout."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Does under-cabinet lighting replace counter recessed lights?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "No, they supplement each other. Recessed counter lights illuminate the front edge of the counter and the person working, while under-cabinet lights illuminate the back edge of the counter and kill any shadows cast by your upper cabinets. Using both creates perfectly shadow-free task lighting."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How far from the wall should I place counter task lights?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Place them roughly 24 inches away from the perimeter wall. Standard lower cabinets are 24 inches deep, with a 25.5-inch countertop depth. Placing the light at 24 inches centers the beam directly over the edge of the workspace so your head and body do not block the light while you are standing there."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do kitchen recessed lights need to be rated for damp locations?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, it is highly recommended to use damp-rated or wet-rated recessed fixtures in a kitchen, especially for the lights positioned directly above the sink, stove, or dishwasher, where they will be exposed to rising steam and moisture."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do I handle a kitchen that opens directly into a dining room?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Always use separate circuits (zones) and dimmers. You can use the same style of recessed fixture in both rooms for visual continuity, but design the dining room for a lower target (like 20-30 FC) and the kitchen for a higher target (50 FC), allowing you to dim the kitchen lights while eating."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do recessed lights work over a kitchen island, or are pendants better?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Both work perfectly well, and it simply depends on your aesthetic preference. Recessed lights provide a clean, modern look that doesn't obstruct sightlines across the kitchen. Pendants act as decorative centerpieces. You can also mix them — using pendants over the island and recessed lights everywhere else."
      }
    }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://calcfordiy.com" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Calculators", "item": "https://calcfordiy.com/calculators" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Recessed Lighting Calculator — Kitchen", "item": "https://calcfordiy.com/calculators/recessed-lights-kitchen" }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4 print:hidden">
    <a href="/" class="hover:text-blue-600">Home</a>
    <span>/</span>
    <a href="/calculators" class="hover:text-blue-600">Calculators</a>
    <span>/</span>
    <span>Recessed Lighting — Kitchen</span>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Recessed Lighting Calculator — Kitchen</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg">Kitchens need two layers of lighting — general ambient light for the whole room and brighter task lighting over counters and islands. This calculator handles both separately.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-4 mb-6 print:bg-white print:border-gray-300">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-1 print:text-gray-900">Kitchen Lighting Needs Two Calculations</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 print:text-gray-700">General ambient lighting targets 30-50 foot-candles for the whole kitchen. Task areas like countertops and islands need 70-100 foot-candles to safely prepare food. Trying to handle both with one set of fixtures leads to either a dim kitchen or an overlit one. This calculator keeps them separate so you can plan zone-controlled lighting.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm p-6 mb-6 print:border-none print:shadow-none print:p-0">

    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 print:text-lg">
      <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold print:hidden">1</span>
      Kitchen Dimensions
    </h2>

    <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg mb-5 print:bg-white print:border print:border-gray-200">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
        <div>
          <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Kitchen Length</label>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <input type="number" id="k_len_ft" placeholder="14" min="0" max="100"
              class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
            <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
            <input type="number" id="k_len_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
              class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
            <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Kitchen Width</label>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <input type="number" id="k_wid_ft" placeholder="12" min="0" max="100"
              class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
            <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
            <input type="number" id="k_wid_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
              class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
            <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <label class="block text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Ceiling Height</label>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <input type="number" id="k_ceil_ft" placeholder="9" min="6" max="20"
            class="w-32 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
          <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">ft</span>
          <input type="number" id="k_ceil_in" placeholder="0" min="0" max="11"
            class="w-16 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500" />
          <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 shrink-0">in</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="my-5 border-gray-200 print:hidden" />

    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 print:text-lg">
      <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold print:hidden">2</span>
      General Ambient Lighting
    </h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-5 print:bg-gray-50 print:p-4 print:rounded-lg print:border print:border-gray-200">
      <div>
        <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-2">Ambient Target</label>
        <select id="ambient_fc"
          class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500">
          <option value="30">30 FC — moderate, task lights handle the rest</option>
          <option value="50" selected>50 FC — standard kitchen ambient</option>
        </select>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1 print:hidden">IES recommendation for kitchen general lighting</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-2">Ambient Fixture Lumens</label>
        <select id="ambient_lumens"
          class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500">
          <option value="650">650 lm — 6" LED standard</option>
          <option value="750" selected>750 lm — 6" LED bright</option>
          <option value="1000">1000 lm — 6" LED high output</option>
        </select>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="my-5 border-gray-200 print:hidden" />

    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 print:text-lg">
      <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold print:hidden">3</span>
